{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17607650","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17607650"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:24:41+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:24:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15967"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15967","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15967"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.83,0.07,0.07,0,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8658"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110493"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8658","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8658"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15967"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92757"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"3514"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8126"},{"type":"tags","id":"10770"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20731"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20735"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110493","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/110493"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EGestational diabetes mellitus (GDM) is glucose intolerance with onset or first recognition during pregnancy. It affects approximately 5-10% of pregnancies and can have significant consequences for both the pregnant woman and the developing fetus.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is most likely to occur as a maternal complication of gestational diabetes mellitus?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Increased risk of pre-eclampsia","Increased risk of neural tube defects","Increased risk of placental abruption","Lower risk of urinary tract infections","Decreased risk of hypertensive disorders"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWomen with gestational diabetes mellitus have an \u003Cstrong\u003Eincreased risk of pre-eclampsia\u003C/strong\u003E. The hyperglycaemic state can cause endothelial dysfunction and inflammation, contributing to the development of hypertensive disorders of pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options represent misconceptions about GDM complications:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased risk of neural tube defects\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily associated with folate deficiency and poorly controlled pre-existing diabetes rather than gestational diabetes. Neural tube defects occur during early embryogenesis (weeks 3-4), typically before GDM develops.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased risk of placental abruption\u003C/strong\u003E is not a recognised complication associated with GDM. While women with pre-existing diabetes may have increased risk of placental complications, the primary placental complication associated with gestational diabetes is placental insufficiency rather than abruption.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELower risk of urinary tract infections\u003C/strong\u003E - GDM increases susceptibility to infections, including urinary tract infections\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased risk of hypertensive disorders\u003C/strong\u003E - GDM is associated with an increased risk of hypertensive disorders during pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Gestational diabetes mellitus increases the risk of pre-eclampsia in pregnant women","Gestational diabetes is associated with multiple maternal complications including hypertensive disorders, caesarean delivery, and future type 2 diabetes"],"references":["Abourawi FI. Diabetes mellitus and pregnancy. Libyan J Med. 2006 Jul 4;1(1):28-41. doi: 10.4176/060617. PMID: 21526019; PMCID: PMC3081498","Plows JF, Stanley JL, Baker PN, Reynolds CM, Vickers MH. The Pathophysiology of Gestational Diabetes Mellitus. Int J Mol Sci. 2018 Oct 26;19(11):3342. doi: 10.3390/ijms19113342. PMID: 30373146; PMCID: PMC6274679","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92757"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15967"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92757","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92757"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-31T15:35:51+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-31T15:35:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8658"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110493"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null